WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:03.000
If you are on a Home page please
click 'Go to texts list' button

00:03.000 --> 00:07.000
Click 'Search & Filter' and expand more properties
for searching

00:07.000 --> 00:10.000
Click to 'Title' edit box and type name, which you
want to find (in my case it's 'geo') and click 'Search'

00:10.000 --> 00:12.500
Take a look at found results

00:12.500 --> 00:17.000
Click on order button near edit box (two triangles)
and select order by descending for example and click 'Search'

00:17.000 --> 00:21.000
Results are ordered. Green circle near 'Search & filter' is green,
which means that filter applied. Yellow light means, that after filter you 
did another changes, which is not applied.

00:21.000 --> 00:25.000
Set order by ascending and click 'Search' button

00:25.000 --> 00:31.000
Light is green, but after change name it becomes yellow
(now title is 'geo bomb'). Click 'Search' button.

00:31.000 --> 00:37.000
You'll see only one result, which corresponds that title.
Select concrete country (the US) and click 'Search'

00:37.000 --> 00:41.000
You still are able to see previous result, because it's American text
Select another country and click 'Search'

00:41.000 --> 00:44.000
There is no text, which corresponds. 

00:44.000 --> 00:49.000
If we get beck to the US, will see previous result (one text)

00:49.000 --> 00:55.000
To remove all filters click button 'Clear'. 
You'll see all texts as a result.
